?topicID=949.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   About Cannipetting</span><hr size=1> im a 53 Magician and ive read alot about cannipetting, after extensive search i did not find the information i was looking for so here goes<br>
<br>
i know the basic principle, summon pet and reclaim pet to gain mana, specialise conjuration very useful...<br>
<br>
so arranged my gear to get the maximum out of it<br>
-regeant conservation 3<br>
-summoning efficiency 3<br>
-mana preservation 3 (crystalline torque)<br>
-my most recent ring (forgot the exact name) for faster casting<br>
-using my Staff Of Elemental Mastery : Water , for the clicky reclaim energy (which will change back to one of the old focuses after i complete my epic)<br>
<br>
so far so good , i tried with MS2 , i tried with my 49 pets (i got air and earth), i tried with my 51 earth and 53 air as well...<br>
<br>
i estimate i gain about 0.8% of my mana bar for each repetition<br>
<br>
i do not have the money atm to buy a horse so i have to choose between cannipetting OR Medding...<br>
<br>
considering the trouble cannipetting involves VS the simple fact of sitting , which would be the most efficient in mana/ticks<br>
<br>
or should i wait till i get enough AA for improved reclaim And/Or Get a Horse<br>
<br>
Leana Dracobones<br>
Magician of the 53rd Circle (+1regen , +2First Aid)<br>
2 pieces away from epic =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=armantuneweaver>Arman Tuneweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#333333>(1/20/03 9:52:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=949.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: About Cannipetting</span><hr size=1> No matter what items you have, you'll gain mana from casting MS2 and reclaiming it.  My bet is that you accidentally were using the wrong spell.<br>
