 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=buppy>Buppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#333333>(1/20/03 10:03:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=949.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: About Cannipetting</span><hr size=1> If you're only gaining 0.8 % then either you're doing something wrong or you have a LOT of mana.<br>
<br>
At 55 with about 2800 mana I gain about 4-6% per cycle. That is with Summoning Efficiency 3, Summoned Focus Ring, reclaiming MS2 with Sol Ro Focus. No AA, spec'd in Evoc. +100 to 150 mana each time. Cycle takes about 10 seconds. Not sure what sitting med rates are, but no where near that quick. Takes me 3 minutes to go from OOM to full chain-reclaiming with no buffs. Sitting is no where near that, even with KEI.<br>
<br>
I doubt you have 12500 mana, so I think you're doing something wrong.<br>
<br>
If you're reclaiming pets at low health, then you want to wait for Improved Reclaim. (At least to my understanding.) If you are chain-reclaiming pets at full health, then do not get IR, get Elemental Pact and Quick Summoning. IR gives back less mana than a regularly reclaimed MS2 pet at full health.<br>
<br>
This may change with proper AA and equipment using 50+ pets, not sure. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Buppyy O'Boom</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
Jester of Justice<br>
