 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A> at: 1/20/03 10:19:55 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krankenthegnome>Kranken the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 345<br> <font color=#333333>(1/20/03 11:33:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=949.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://saedyan.freesehttp://pages.prodigy.net/cohmsford/america.gifrvers.com/images/pstgif.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: About Cannipetting</span><hr size=1> By the way, IRE actually <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>hurts</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> cannipetting.. just get a horse <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>------------<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=433620">Kranken</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->63 Arch Mage<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Xev<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->&quot;Where's my pet..?&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2721<br> <font color=#333333>(1/21/03 12:04:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=949.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: About Cannipetting</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Improved Reclaim Energy</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> does reduce the amount of mana returned when doing pure reclamation, but has some advantages:<br>
<br>
1) Since the amount of mana returned is based solely on the nominal mana cost, you can use a fighting pet to reclaim, instead of having to mem <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Monster Summoning 2</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Greater Conjuration: Earth</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  This frees up a spell slot and makes you less vulnerable while reclaiming, as you will likely be in the midst of summoning a fighting pet, not a lesser one.<br>
<br>
2) It lets you reclaim a wounded pet for full mana.  This can be useful when soloing, reclaiming a heavily injured pet rather than healing it or waiting for it to regenerate.  Some mages have even master chaining pets but reclaiming the injured pet for mana instead of simply <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>/pet go away</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (but not me).  In multi-pet groups <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Improved Reclaim Energy</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">shines</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.  Before each pet dies, it is is reclaimed for full mana, allowing a mage group to sustain HPS nearly forever without using much mana.<br>
<br>
3) It does not hurt straight reclaims for mana as much as most people believe.  Recent tests put it at about 125 mana per reclaim, which is quite respectable.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 655<br> <font color=#333333>(1/21/03 7:24:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=949.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: About Cannipetting</span><hr size=1> Hey Balanz son of Anz, how much percent mana net gain do you get from reclaming a pet, and how much does it take to cast? <p>Happy trails.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2723<br> <font color=#333333>(1/21/03 6:18:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=949.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: About Cannipetting</span><hr size=1> I never look at mana %'s, as I find them unreliable and distracting.  In my opinion, the %'s shown I consider to be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;displayed mana&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as distinct from <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;actual mana&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> which I take to done serverside.<br>
<br>
When I am interested in knowing something, I perform experiments, for example, counting the number of pet summons it takes to empty my mana bar with and without summoning efficiency.<br>
<br>
Here is my best estimate of an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>IRE</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> reclaim gain.<br>
<br>
Cost is 400 base mana.<br>
<br>
Reductions are:<br>
<br>
10% or 40 mana for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Specialization: Conjuration 200%</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
15% or 60 mana for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Spell Casting Mastery 3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
13% or 52 mana for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Summoning Efficiency 3</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Or 248 mana to cast <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Greater Vocaration: Earth</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, my usual reclaim pet.<br>
<br>
So far as anyone can tell, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Improved Reclaim Energy</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> returns 100% of the mana cost, call it 99% <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>(too close to tell)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  So it returns 396 mana.<br>
<br>
396 - 248 = 148 mana per reclaim.<br>
<br>
Not everyone agrees with my figures, but they are good enough for government work, and match my observations and readings well enough.<br>
<br>
At worse, it is at least 100 mana per reclaim.<br>
<br>
